Turkey Stocks: Celebi Hava Servisi, Usas Ucak Move in Istanbul

-- B y   S e l c u k   G o k o l u k
-- 
2011-12-06T16:03:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-06/turkey-stocks-celebi-hava-servisi-usas-ucak-move-in-istanbul.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  fell 0.9 percent to 54,679.11 at 5:30 p.m. in Istanbul,
declining for the first day in three.  The following stocks were active on the Turkish stock
market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Celebi Hava Servisi AS (CLEBI)  , an airport ground
services operator, fell 1.3 percent to 18.90 liras. Celebi’s
parent Celebi Havacilik Holding AS will buy Fraport Ground
Service Austria GMBH, which serves Vienna international airport,
Celebi Hava said in a filing with the Istanbul Stock Exchange
today. Fraport Ground Service has capital of 4.4 million euros,
it said.  Usas Ucak Servisi AS (UCAK)  , a Turkish airline caterer,
advanced 7.8 percent to 2.91 liras, the biggest rise in almost
four months. Owner Gate Gourmet Participations Espana SL sold
its 56.3 percent stake in Usas to Turkraft Holding AS for 61.4
million liras, Usas said in a filing with the exchange today.
The stake is worth 56 million liras, according to the current
share price, Bloomberg data showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
